cs.IT, cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.MM

The paper deals with the sharing of secret keys in wireless networks, which involves information theory, cryptography, and networking. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory), which deals with the fundamental limits of communication and information processing. The paper also discusses security and attacks, which suggests the category cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The use of Wi-Fi networks and the IEEE 802.11 standard suggests the category cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The development of an adaptive rate allocation policy and explicit constructions for ARQ secrecy coding suggests the category cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the mention of a Linux-based prototype suggests the category cs.MM (Multimedia).
